<div hidden
     class="fixed inset-0 z-50 opacity-0 pointer-events-none transition-opacity duration-200"
     data-controller="modal"
     data-modal-auto-open-value="true"
     data-action="click->modal#backdropClick keydown@window->modal#escape open-modal@window->modal#open">
  <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black/50 dark:bg-black/70"></div>
  <div class="relative flex items-center justify-center min-h-full p-4">
    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-xl shadow-2xl w-full max-w-xl max-h-[85dvh] flex flex-col border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 relative"
         data-modal-target="panel">

      <button data-action="click->modal#close"
              class="absolute top-3 right-3 z-10 w-7 h-7 flex items-center justify-center rounded-md hover:bg-gray-100 dark:hover:bg-gray-800 text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 cursor-pointer text-lg leading-none">✕</button>

      <div class="overflow-y-auto px-5 pt-8 pb-4 space-y-6 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 font-serif">

        <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-3 text-center">
          <img src="/icon2.png" class="w-16 h-16 rounded-2xl shadow-sm" alt="Finesse Chat">
          <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
          This microapp was built to demonstrate the practical differences inline 
          <span class="text-blue-600">Polling</span>,
          <span class="text-amber-500">WebSockets</span>,
          and
          <span class="text-teal-600">Server-Sent Events</span>
          .
          </p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500">built with Rails 8, Hotwire, and Go</p>
        </div>

        <section>
          <h3 class="font-semibold font-sans text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 mb-2">The Three Transports</h3>
          <div class="space-y-2">
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-950/40 px-3 py-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-600">Polling</span> performs a fetch every 7.77 seconds. The simplest approach — very reliable, but not real-time. A great baseline and fallback.</div>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-950/40 px-3 py-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300"><span class="text-amber-500">WebSockets</span> via SolidCable — lowest latency, but more finicky with ordered data and reconnects. The fastest but least reliable transport in testing.</div>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-teal-200 dark:border-teal-800 bg-teal-50 dark:bg-teal-950/40 px-3 py-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300"><span class="text-teal-600">Server-Sent Events</span> over a long-lived HTTP connection — browsers handle it natively, reliable delivery, and this app demonstrates its speed advantage over WebSockets.</div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <h3 class="font-semibold font-sans text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 mb-2">Features</h3>
        <section>
          <button class="btn-storm w-full mb-3 pointer-events-none select-none justify-center text-sm py-2" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true">
            <span class="bolt-zap">⚡</span> Bot Storm
          </button>
          <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-2">
            Inside the app, the Bot Storm button will fire a burst of messages from bots to demonstrate how each transport handles message flooding.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-2">
            When using <span class="font-sans inline-block px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-semibold bg-amber-500 text-white">WebSockets</span>, you can expect to see messages tagged with an <span class="font-sans inline-block px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-semibold bg-amber-400/20 text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400 border border-amber-300 dark:border-amber-600">OUT OF ORDER</span> badge. This demonstrates that WebSockets messages have a decent potential of being received out of order.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h3 class="font-semibold font-sans text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 mb-2">Tips</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-1.5 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>The chat resets every five minutes — the channel name rotates on each reset</li>
            <li>Most markdown is supported — **bold**, `code`, *italic*, and more</li>
            <li>Press <kbd class="font-sans px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 font-mono text-xs">↑</kbd> in the empty input to edit your last message</li>
            <li>Hover one of your messages to reveal edit/delete controls</li>
            <li>Click the ↺ icon next to your username to get a new random username</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h3 class="font-semibold font-sans text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 mb-2">Slash Commands</h3>
          <dl class="space-y-1.5">
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <dt class="font-mono text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 shrink-0 w-32">/help</dt>
              <dd>Show a list of commands in chat</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <dt class="font-mono text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 shrink-0 w-32">/time</dt>
              <dd>Post the current server time</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <dt class="font-mono text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 shrink-0 w-32">/meow, /🐱</dt>
              <dd>Thanks for signing up for Cat Facts!</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <dt class="font-mono text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 shrink-0 w-32">/woof, /🐶</dt>
              <dd>Dog Facts for the refined factician</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <dt class="font-mono text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 shrink-0 w-32">/wut &lt;acronym&gt;</dt>
              <dd>Expand a tech acronym</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <dt class="font-mono text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 shrink-0 w-32">/me &lt;action&gt;</dt>
              <dd>Post a third-person action</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </section>

      </div>

      <div class="px-5 py-3 border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 shrink-0 flex items-center justify-between gap-4">
        <label class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 cursor-pointer select-none">
          <input type="checkbox" checked
                 class="w-3.5 h-3.5 rounded accent-teal-600 cursor-pointer"
                 data-modal-target="showOnLaunch"
                 data-action="change->modal#toggleShowOnLaunch">
          Show on launch
        </label>
        <button data-action="click->modal#close"
                class="px-4 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-teal-600 hover:bg-teal-500 text-white text-xs font-semibold transition-colors cursor-pointer">
          Start chatting
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
